SIMPLE: overshoot
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overshoot
<hw>O`ver*shoot"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Overshot</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overshooting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
shoot over or beyond; to miss; <as>as, to <ex>overshoot</ex> a mark; to
<ex>overshoot</ex> the green in golf</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Not to
<xex>overshoot</xex> his game.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>To go beyond an intended
point or limit; <as>as, to <ex>overshoot</ex> the runway in landing an
airplane; to <ex>overshoot</ex> the endpoint in a
titration</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To pass swiftly over; to fly beyond.</def>
<rj><au>Hartle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To exceed; <as>as, to <ex>overshoot</ex> the
truth</as>.</def> <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To overshoot one's self</b></col>, <cd>to venture too
far; to assert too much.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overshoot</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overshoot
<hw>O`ver*shoot"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To fly beyond the
mark.</def> <rj><au>Collier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overshot</ent>⟦br⟧
